						<p>Even better, instead of <em>only</em> landing in Sydney (where cables on the east coast of Australia usually land), it was also landing in the Sunshine Coast, Queensland — our backyard.</p>
						<p>Normally, subsea operators don’t deal with small startups (which we were).</p>
						<p>But RTI were no normal company and Russ Matulich (CEO) was no normal leader. He loved the idea of what OneQode was doing and took the time to help us through the process of getting capacity on their cables.</p>
						<p>Thanks to them, we were soon preparing to deploy our equipment in the Sunshine Coast, Tokyo and Guam to leverage our new capacity.</p>
