						<h2 class="mt-4">You can’t do it from behind a computer screen </h2>
						<p>Doing this during a pandemic was odd, to say the least.</p>
						<p>Every single step of the project was affected — from factory shutdowns and global supply shortages to customs delays and interstate travel.</p>
						<p><strong>Thing is, you can’t build a global network from behind a computer screen.</strong> You need boots on the ground to build servers, package and ship things, install equipment and plug stuff in, as well as replace broken hardware in the middle of the night.</p>
						<p>With travel restrictions preventing key staff from travelling interstate and overseas, we had to improvise.</p>
